{
  "stem": "26276.3",
  "chunk_idx": 7,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 9.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "His belly opened up like a chicken and the pieces fell down into the water.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "In Dachau, you had the camp was surrounded with a deep concrete wall, half of it filled up with water after the electric barbed wires, in case somebody wanted to try to escape.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "First you couldn't because the wire was electrified, so you would get burned right there to death.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And if you do go through, you have to go into that water.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "There was no way of anybody to climb up on a straight concrete wall to get out towards another fence.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "After the fence, that was why the German was up there in those guard houses.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And I remember pieces of that SS falling into that water.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "The water turned red like blood.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "That was my biggest pleasure that I had for my parents, for my brothers and sisters, and for everybody, that I was able to pay back a little bit for the tortures that they had to go through.",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Nothing.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Not a word.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "It made me so mad.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Like I was like  a wild dog to see just a man who killed yesterday to wear one of the uniforms today to try to camouflage himself so he could escape that I didn't have any-- I just couldn't ask or say anything.",
      "word_count": 43
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I mean everybody-- it was not just me-- but whoever was able to run around, was strong enough to walk around, everybody was trying to take advantage of that because most of them were still sick.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "There was typhoid.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "I was over it.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "I survived it with no doctor's care, no medicine.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "People died by the thousands every single day.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "Dachau had 33,000 to 34,000 prisoners.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Mm-hmm.",
      "word_count": 1
    }
  ],
